beast:pv.name: TEST-BST0:HIGH-SWITCH
beast:pv.beast:description: Whenever the HIGH switch gets wet, the pump will be forced ON

beast:guidance.beast:title: In the event that the MID switch has failed
beast:guidance.beast:details: The tank level has continued to increase and has reached the HIGH level generating a MAJOR alarm

beast:guidance.beast:title: Consequence of deviation
beast:guidance.beast:details: The MID switch fails to operate: defective switch, blocked switch or damaged wiring. As a consequence the pump remaining dormant, the tank will overflow, causing inconvenience and damage to property.

beast:guidance.beast:title: Time for response
beast:guidance.beast:details: The tank will overflow if the pump fails to be forced ON in 10 minutes

beast:automated_action.beast:title: Contact Maintenance Service
beast:automated_action.beast:details: mailto:someone@iter.org,someone_else@iter.org?subject=*MID Switch fails to maintain the tank level&body=*{0} alarm - Tank Switch is {1}

beast:pv.name: TEST-BST0:LOW-SWITCH
beast:pv.beast:description: Whenever the LOW switch becomes dry, the pump will be forced OFF

beast:guidance.beast:title: In the event that the MID switch has failed
beast:guidance.beast:details: The tank level has continued to decrease and has reached the LOW level generating a MAJOR alarm

beast:guidance.beast:title: Consequence of deviation
beast:guidance.beast:details: The MID switch fails. The outcome is simple, the pump will drain the tank until it is empty, whereupon it will try to pump air indefinitely and burn out. Unfortunately, every time a MID switch fails for too long, a new pump may have to be installed

beast:guidance.beast:title: Corrective action
beast:guidance.beast:details: Change the MID Switch and check if the pump has already burned out

beast:guidance.beast:title: Time for response
beast:guidance.beast:details: The pump will burn out in 30 minutes
